1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,545
<i>Don't think for a second</i>

2
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:06,005
<i>that I've forgotten about</i>
<i>what you did to my brother.</i>

3
00:00:06,089 --> 00:00:09,217
<i>Your brother died because of you.</i>

4
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:10,176
[BOTH GRUNTING]

5
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,219
<i>No!</i>

6
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:14,180
[OVERLAPPING GRUNTING
AND SCREAMING]

7
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:16,349
- Go after them!
- [WOMAN] Liam!

8
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,517
Enough!

9
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,394
[OLSEN AND DADO GRUNTING]

10
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:22,689
- [OLSEN GROANS]
- [ICE WHIMPERS]

11
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,566
<i>Don't hurt him anymore! Please!</i>

12
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:27,944
[LIAM] <i>So you're still alive.</i>

13
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:29,571
[GWEN] <i>You're dead.</i>

14
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:37,412
<i>- There's nowhere to hide here.</i>
- [LUNA] <i>The ceiling.</i>

15
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:38,621
<i>Hurry.</i>

16
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:41,833
<i>We're out of time. Move faster.</i>

17
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:44,127
- [LOUD WHIMPER]
<i>- Shh!</i>

18
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:48,339
[HOMER] <i>Did you ever love me, Wendy?</i>

19
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:49,799
[WENDY] <i>I tried.</i>

20
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,551
<i>I loved you.</i>

21
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:53,595
<i>You screwed me over.</i>
<i>Just like Magnus!</i>

22
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:55,472
<i>Maybe you two are working together.</i>

23
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:58,183
<i>Maybe you tipped off the police,</i>
<i>and that's why I got caught.</i>

24
00:00:58,266 --> 00:00:59,684
<i>I don't know what you're talking about!</i>

25
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:00,935
<i>- Wendy--</i>
<i>- You bastard!</i>

26
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:02,520
[BOTH GROAN]

27
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,064
- [LUCAS] <i>Hit him!</i>
- [WENDY] <i>Stop it!</i>

28
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,191
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

29
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,235
<i>You can't kill him yet.</i>

30
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,653
<i>We still need him.</i>

31
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,114
[BOTH GRUNT]

32
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,617
<i>- Luna?</i>
<i>- Liam?</i>

33
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:19,412
- [HAPPY] <i>Sir Liam.</i>
<i>- Ms. Happy. Joy!</i>

34
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:21,498
<i>Boss Emil!</i>

35
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:23,208
<i>We've got a problem.</i>

36
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:26,085
[EMIL] <i>Liam Roja.</i>

37
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:29,506
<i>If you aren't back here in five minutes,</i>

38
00:01:30,673 --> 00:01:32,550
<i>you know what'll happen to your mom.</i>

39
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:46,523
[LUNA] Liam.

40
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:55,949
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:04,791
We're cooking.

42
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:10,338
We're making a dish using
whatever ingredients are here.

43
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:12,966
The fastest, the tastiest,

44
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:14,717
and enough for a lot of people.

45
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,052
Sir Liam!

46
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,763
We're going to cook
in the middle of all this danger?

47
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:20,515
This is what's going to save us.

48
00:02:20,598 --> 00:02:23,393
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

49
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,019
Doc.

50
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:27,605
I need you to get
the most important ingredient.

51
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:32,819
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,696
I'll be back.

53
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:36,197
- Luna?
- Dude.

54
00:02:37,448 --> 00:02:40,201
They need to be drawn in
by the smell of your cooking.

55
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:41,828
You can do it.

56
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,497
Be careful.

57
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,041
You too.

58
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,045
Go--

59
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:06,853
{\an8}[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:42,847
{\an8}[MINNIE COUGHING]

61
00:03:49,145 --> 00:03:50,355
{\an8}Hon.

62
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:52,815
{\an8}Thank you.

63
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:56,486
{\an8}- Daddy.
- Mm?

64
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,821
{\an8}Mommy's sick again.

65
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:00,281
{\an8}[GULPS]

66
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:01,699
{\an8}No, baby.

67
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:04,661
{\an8}Mommy can handle this.

68
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:07,872
{\an8}Remember my promise to you?

69
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:10,208
{\an8}That we'll get back home?

70
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,501
{\an8}Yes.

71
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:13,836
{\an8}Yes.

72
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:21,636
{\an8}[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:40,947
{\an8}[PANTING]

74
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,742
{\an8}Looks like it's still deep.

75
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:51,541
{\an8}Engineer, how far are we from our target?

76
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,960
{\an8}Hold on, I'll check.

77
00:04:55,420 --> 00:05:01,926
{\an8}[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

78
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:19,485
{\an8}More or less three meters left.

79
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:22,864
{\an8}We're about to reach the old sewage pipe.

80
00:05:24,532 --> 00:05:26,451
{\an8}Once you break through that,

81
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:29,454
{\an8}you'll have an exit path
out of this hospital.

82
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:35,960
{\an8}[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:38,671
{\an8}The soil texture is changing.

84
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,592
{\an8}When it gets loamy and soft like this,
you can't use explosives anymore.

85
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,802
{\an8}The tunnel could collapse.

86
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:51,726
{\an8}[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

87
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:04,405
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:31,140
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:41,484
Get in, hurry!

90
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:43,820
You're moving too slow.

91
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:48,491
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

92
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:49,617
Uno.

93
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:52,870
They tried to play us.

94
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:54,747
Kneel down!

95
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:56,791
- Son!
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

96
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:58,334
Olsen!

97
00:06:58,417 --> 00:07:02,296
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:04,006
They managed to sneak in guns.

99
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,634
They're smart.

100
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,228
He's your son?

101
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:23,901
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,173
Just don't move too far.
This won't explode.

103
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:53,347
- Tres.
- What?

104
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:54,599
We're out of bombs.

105
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:56,142
What about this one?

106
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:57,226
That'll do.

107
00:07:58,603 --> 00:07:59,937
If he tries to fight back again,

108
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:03,357
his mother blows up.

109
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:09,071
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,239
[RAPID FOOTSTEPS]

111
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,074
- [MAN 1] What's that?!
- [MAN 2] Drop it!

112
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:13,201
Liam?

113
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:14,160
[GRETA] Son!

114
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,411
Liam.

115
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:19,415
Move.

116
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,751
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

117
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,544
Walk!

118
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:28,841
- [THWACKS]
- [GRETA SCREAMS]

119
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,551
- [LIAM GRUNTS]
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

120
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,803
Son! [WHIMPERS]

121
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:39,644
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

122
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:50,196
Chef Luna, what are we cooking?

123
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,659
Guys.

124
00:08:54,742 --> 00:08:56,118
[HISSES]

125
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:02,250
We need a dish that's mouthwatering
just from the aroma.

126
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:04,794
Any thoughts?

127
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:09,131
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,258
Uh…

129
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,306
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

130
00:09:19,684 --> 00:09:20,893
[GASPS]

131
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:23,604
Garlic chicken mushroom.

132
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:25,773
[EXHALES] The restaurant-style one?

133
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:27,358
Yes.

134
00:09:27,441 --> 00:09:28,943
Chef Liam's style.

135
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:31,696
Just the aroma alone,
and they won't stand a chance.

136
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:34,156
High-heat sauté, heavy on the garlic.

137
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:37,702
Joy, chop lots of garlic
and lots of onions.

138
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:41,038
And you, chop the bell peppers, broccoli,
potatoes, and mushrooms.

139
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:43,708
- Yes, Chef.
- Guys, this will be quick.

140
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:45,459
- We've got this.
- Yes, Chef.

141
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:47,128
- Yes, Chef.
- Okay.

142
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:50,548
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

143
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:54,719
Where are your companions?

144
00:09:54,802 --> 00:10:00,308
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:02,727
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]
- [MAGNUS] Wait--

146
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:05,062
- [LIAM GRUNTS]
- Hey! Wait! Hey!

147
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:07,648
- [MAGNUS] Liam!
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

148
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,525
[CHOPPING]

149
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:13,154
- Chef, should it be like this, or bigger?
- Okay.

150
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:14,989
Like this, Chef?

151
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:16,240
That's the size.

152
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:21,662
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

153
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,456
- You got it?
- Copy, Chef.

154
00:10:23,539 --> 00:10:24,749
I'll do that.

155
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,877
- [DADO GRUNTS]
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

156
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,755
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- [LIAM COUGHS]

157
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:33,090
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:37,053
Chef, should I add more?

159
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:39,889
- Is this enough?
- Uh…

160
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,682
- That's the last one.
- Okay.

161
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:44,852
- So, after that, the broccoli.
- All right.

162
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:46,520
Think you're tough, huh?!

163
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,064
- [GROANS]
- [GRETA] Enough!

164
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:49,607
- Think you're tough, huh?!
- [GRUNTS]

165
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:50,941
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]
- [GRUNTS]

166
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:54,362
[LIAM PANTING]

167
00:10:55,237 --> 00:11:00,910
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:05,498
Now, you're tame.

169
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:06,666
[COUGHS]

170
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:10,419
I'll ask you one last time.

171
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:11,671
[PANTS]

172
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:13,631
Where are your companions?

173
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:20,846
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

174
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:28,646
[CHOPPING]

175
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:34,068
They're hiding in the commissary.

176
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:37,696
[LIAM BREATHES HEAVILY, GRUNTS]

177
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,323
- Are you lying?
- [GRUNTS]

178
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,325
Huh?!

179
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:45,162
What do you think, boss?

180
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,917
- Check it out.
- Yes, sir!

181
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,213
Stand up!

182
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:56,715
Stand!

183
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:59,343
[GRUNTS]

184
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:06,100
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:08,644
If your son is fooling me,

186
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,397
he'll come back to you as a corpse.

187
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:15,818
- Liam, please…
- Go ahead!

188
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,154
- Walk now!
- Hurry!

189
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:21,615
- Hurry!
- Greta!

190
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:27,872
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,461
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:34,670
[PLATE CLINKS]

193
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:37,756
[SIZZLE]

194
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,385
This is the powder.

195
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:45,931
Shall we add this, Chef?

196
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:52,855
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

197
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:58,819
Add all of that.

198
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:01,113
[CLINKING]

199
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,454
Hold on, Ms. Happy.

200
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:09,538
- [SCRAPES]
- [CHUCKLES]

201
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:14,835
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:16,879
- Go on, taste it.
- All right.

203
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:18,047
- Here.
- Hmm.

204
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,091
Chef, here.

205
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,723
- Smells good.
- Hmm.

206
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:29,850
- It's been so long since I--
- [DOOR OPENS]

207
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:33,187
Doc! Hmm.

208
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,106
I got it.

209
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,025
Okay.

210
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:40,444
Hmm.

211
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,364
Hmm?

212
00:13:46,283 --> 00:13:47,493
Uh--

213
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:53,207
[CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

214
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,125
It's good.

215
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,002
R-Really?

216
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,174
That was my mom's specialty.

217
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,135
That's the last thing she cooked for us

218
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:08,973
before she died from leukemia.

219
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:12,351
She was the reason I became a doctor.

220
00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:15,354
Um… Sorry, Doc.

221
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:16,814
I didn't know.

222
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:20,192
Uh, I'm sure…

223
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,403
your mother would be very proud of you.

224
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:24,697
Thank you.

225
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:29,076
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

226
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,328
So? Let's do it?

227
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:35,165
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:37,001
I hope this works.

229
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:57,521
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:02,902
Chef, stir it in.

231
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,827
Keep an eye on them.

232
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,669
- I'll leave it to you.
- Yes, boss.

233
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:31,263
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:33,933
[DARK MUSIC STINGS]

235
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:36,477
<i>Are you pregnant, Wendy?</i>

236
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,188
<i>Oh, I'm not.</i>

237
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:41,649
<i>False alarm.</i>

238
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,525
<i>I loved you.</i>

239
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,654
<i>I dreamed of having children with you.</i>

240
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:48,614
<i>But what did you do?</i>

241
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,575
<i>I'm glad we didn't have a child.</i>

242
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:57,164
<i>I'd have felt bad for the kid,</i>
<i>having a father like you.</i>

243
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:07,049
Are you okay?

244
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:13,263
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

245
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:14,640
When we…

246
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,560
When we were in the staff house…

247
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:23,273
Papa's urn shattered.

248
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:28,112
Why was it filled with sand?

249
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,282
I don't know.

250
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,077
You don't?

251
00:16:38,914 --> 00:16:40,082
You don't know.

252
00:16:45,295 --> 00:16:46,672
I know you, Ma.

253
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:50,843
I know when you're not telling the truth.

254
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:57,474
You didn't tell me what happened
between you and Sir Magnus.

255
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:01,437
Are you going to keep this from me too?

256
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,066
It doesn't matter, son.

257
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:10,404
All you need to know is that
he's a good-for-nothing man.

258
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:15,284
My father… isn't dead?

259
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:20,706
Is he really dead, or is he still alive?

260
00:17:20,789 --> 00:17:26,086
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,796
He's alive?

262
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:32,301
Ma.

263
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:42,227
You made me act like a fool all my life?

264
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:51,028
You made me believe that I didn't
have a father. That he'd died.

265
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,615
Every day, every night,

266
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,785
before sleeping, after waking up,

267
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:00,621
I prayed to some sand.

268
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:04,583
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,168
Olsen, I'm sorry.

270
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:09,463
I don't need an apology, Ma.
I don't need it.

271
00:18:12,424 --> 00:18:13,675
Tell me the truth.

272
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:17,471
Tell me the truth.
That's all I'm asking for.

273
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:20,891
You're hiding a lot of things from me.

274
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:26,396
The name that you told me,

275
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:28,857
is it really his name?

276
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:33,195
Is he still alive? Who's my real father?

277
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:35,739
Well?

278
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:41,286
Who's my father? Tell me the truth.

279
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:45,582
Why don't you tell him?

280
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:52,214
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:07,146
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:08,480
[DADO] Hurry up.

283
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:14,695
Pull a fast one on me again
and I'll shoot you myself.

284
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:17,281
Go!

285
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:27,624
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:35,007
{\an8}<i>If you're wondering who your father is,</i>

287
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:39,469
{\an8}<i>I'm also wondering if you're my son.</i>

288
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:42,222
{\an8}<i>All of you, line up now!</i>

289
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:43,307
{\an8}<i>Boss, this looks good.</i>

290
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:45,976
{\an8}<i>Get us plates! Hurry!</i>

291
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:49,688
{\an8}[HOMER] <i>If I lose,</i>
<i>I will let your mother go.</i>

292
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:53,400
{\an8}<i>If I beat you, I'll push your mother</i>
<i>off the building!</i>

293
00:19:53,483 --> 00:19:57,654
{\an8}[GRUNTING]

294
00:19:57,738 --> 00:20:00,866
{\an8}[MEN JEERING]

295
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:02,826
{\an8}[COUGHS]

296
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:06,288
{\an8}[GRUNTING]

297
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:08,040
{\an8}[LIAM] <i>He's going to kill us</i>
<i>once they wake up!</i>

298
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,000
{\an8}[GUNSHOT]

299
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:12,878
{\an8}<i>If someone makes a mistake or commits</i>
<i>a sin, they will be punished.</i>

300
00:20:12,961 --> 00:20:17,674
{\an8}[RAPID GUNSHOTS]

301
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:21,762
{\an8}[RAPID GUNSHOTS]

302
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:24,348
{\an8}[OLSEN] <i>Is he really my father?</i>

303
00:20:26,141 --> 00:20:32,856
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

